# Creating aesthetic mappings in ggplot

## We define the mapping with `aes()`

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(
  data = sun_hours,
  mapping = aes(x = date, y = sun_hours, colour = city)
) + geom_line(size = 2)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](01-Aesthetic-mappings_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-5-1.png){fig-align='center' width=960}
:::
:::

## We define the mapping with `aes()`

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(
  data = sun_hours,
  mapping = aes(x = date, y = city, colour = sun_hours)
) + geom_point(size = 5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](01-Aesthetic-mappings_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-6-1.png){fig-align='center' width=960}
:::
:::

## We frequently omit argument names

<br>

Long form, all arguments are named:

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(
  data = sun_hours,
  mapping = aes(x = date, y = city, colour = sun_hours)
) + geom_point(size = 5)
```
:::

<br>

Abbreviated form, common arguments remain unnamed:

::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(sun_hours, aes(x = date, y = city, colour = sun_hours)) + 
  geom_point(size = 5)
```
:::

## The geom determines how the data is shown

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(sun_hours, aes(date, sun_hours, colour = city)) + 
  geom_line(size = 2)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](01-Aesthetic-mappings_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-9-1.png){fig-align='center' width=960}
:::
:::

## The geom determines how the data is shown

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(sun_hours, aes(date, city, colour = sun_hours)) + 
  geom_point(size = 5)
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](01-Aesthetic-mappings_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-10-1.png){fig-align='center' width=960}
:::
:::


## The geom determines how the data is shown




::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(sun_hours, aes(month, sun_hours, colour = city)) + 
  geom_boxplot()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](01-Aesthetic-mappings_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-12-1.png){fig-align='center' width=960}
:::
:::


## The geom determines how the data is shown

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(sun_hours, aes(month, sun_hours, fill = city)) + 
  geom_violin() +
  facet_wrap(vars(city))
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](01-Aesthetic-mappings_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-13-1.png){fig-align='center' width=960}
:::
:::

# Important: `colour` and `fill` apply to different elements

## `colour` and `fill` apply to different elements

:::{.incremental}

- `colour` applies colour to points, lines, text, borders

- `fill` applies colour to any filled areas

:::

## Many geoms have both `colour` and `fill` aesthetics

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(sun_hours, aes(month, sun_hours, colour = city)) + 
  geom_boxplot()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](01-Aesthetic-mappings_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-14-1.png){fig-align='center' width=960}
:::
:::


## Many geoms have both `colour` and `fill` aesthetics

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(sun_hours, aes(month, sun_hours, fill = city)) + 
  geom_boxplot()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](01-Aesthetic-mappings_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-15-1.png){fig-align='center' width=960}
:::
:::


## Many geoms have both `colour` and `fill` aesthetics

::: {.cell layout-align="center"}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(sun_hours, aes(month, sun_hours, colour = city, fill = city)) + 
  geom_boxplot()
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
